III. Online Support Sessions and Remote Assistance

Q8: How do I request an online session or remote support from ACT?

A: ACT offers remote support sessions to help diagnose and resolve issues more efficiently. You can request an online session in the following ways:

Through the Support form: When opening a ticket, check the box labeled "Request Remote Session" and select your preferred time slot. Our support team will send you a calendar invitation with the session details.

During a Phone Call: If you are speaking with a support engineer by phone, simply ask them to initiate a remote session. They can set up the connection immediately.

Via Email: Include "Request for Remote Session" in the subject line of your support email, and suggest 2-3 time slots that work best for you.

Via Live Chat: Use the live chat feature in the support page to request a remote session, and our team will coordinate the details with you in real-time.

Q9: What do I need to prepare for an online support session?

A: To ensure a productive and efficient remote support session, please prepare the following:

System Access: Ensure you have administrative or sufficient access to the system that needs to be diagnosed. The support engineer may need to access certain screens, logs, or configuration settings.

Stable Internet Connection: A reliable, high-speed internet connection is essential for a smooth remote session. Avoid connecting via mobile hotspot if possible.

Contact Information: Have your phone number ready in case the support engineer needs to call you during the session.

Documentation: Gather any relevant documentation, such as recent error messages, system logs, configuration files, or screenshots that relate to the issue.

Availability: Ensure that the person(s) who will participate in the session are available at the scheduled time. If possible, have someone from your IT team and the relevant business user present.

Quiet Environment: Choose a quiet location where you can focus on the session without distractions or background noise.

Browser Compatibility: If the session will be conducted through a web-based remote access tool, ensure your browser is compatible and that you have the latest version installed.

